general_perception.description and explanation: In the observed traffic image, there are parked sedans on the right side of the road, though their colors are indistinct due to low lighting. These stationary vehicles reduce the usable width of the driving lane but do not pose an immediate dynamic threat. There are no visible pedestrians, cyclists, or motorcyclists, so no immediate action is required, although caution is advised for any that might suddenly appear from behind parked vehicles or off-road areas. Additionally, no traffic signs are visible because of the low visibility conditions, so the ego car should follow default road rules and proceed cautiously. There are no visible traffic lights, which means the ego car should not expect to approach any traffic light-controlled intersections imminently. Orange traffic cones line the right side of the road, forming a pathway and indicating a section of the road or potential hazard is blocked off, possibly due to road work or temporary obstructions, guiding where the ego car should drive. A reflective construction barrier is also present on the right side of the road past the parked cars, suggesting a potential narrowing or blockage in the driving path ahead. Lastly, due to the low visibility conditions, no other discernible objects are noticeable, warranting extra caution to avoid hidden hazards.

1.description and explanation: A parked car is situated on the side of the road. It appears to be stationary, and its position on the edge of the road signals that it is likely not an immediate obstacle for moving traffic. The ego car would need to ensure that it maintains a safe distance from this parked car when driving past to avoid any collisions, paying particular attention if it were to pull out or if someone were to open a car door into the lane of the ego car.

driving_suggestion: Proceed with caution at a reduced speed due to low visibility and possible narrowing of driving lane ahead. Use the vehicle's lighting system to its fullest capacity to improve visibility and be prepared to stop or maneuver if the pathway is obstructed. Stay alert for any unexpected obstacles or road users that might appear from between parked cars or from the sides of the road. Prepare for potential maneuvering around the area marked off by the traffic cones while respecting any road work or obstructions. Utilize the vehicle's lights to improve visibility and alertness of the ego car's presence to other road users.
